{
  "abstract": "Mycotoxins are highly toxic metabolites produced by a number of fungi especially in\r\ndrought-prone environments, unseasonably rainy environments, or high moisture at precrop\r\nharvest, harvest, and storage. The toxins, e.g. aflatoxins, deteriorate food quality, are\r\nbarriers to international trade, pose serious risk to health, and have caused several deaths in\r\nAfrica and Asia.............",
